Author-Name:  Guy Michaels 
Author-Name:  Ferdinand Rauch 
Author-Name:  Stephen J. Redding 
Title: Urbanization and Structural Transformation
Abstract:
 We examine urbanization using new data that allow us to track the
 evolution of population in rural and urban areas in the United States from
 1880 to 2000. We find a positive correlation between initial population
 density and subsequent population growth for intermediate densities, which
 increases the dispersion of the population density distribution over time.
 We use theory and empirical evidence to show this pattern of population
 growth is the result of differences in agriculture's initial share of
 employment across population densities, combined with structural
 transformation that shifts employment away from agriculture.  Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
