Author-Name:  Brian Merlob 
Author-Name:  Charles R. Plott 
Author-Name:  Yuanjun Zhang 
Title: The CMS Auction: Experimental Studies of a Median-Bid Procurement Auction with Nonbinding Bids
Abstract:
 We report on the experimental results of simple auctions with (i) a
 median-bid pricing rule and (ii) nonbinding bids (winning bids can be
 withdrawn)--the two central pillars of the competitive bidding program
 designed by the Centers for Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS).
 Comparisons between the performance of the CMS auction and the performance
 of the excluded-bid auction reveal the problematic nature of the CMS
 auction. The CMS auction fails to generate competitive prices of goods and
 fails to satisfy demand. In all proposed efficiency measures, we find the
 excluded-bid auction significantly outperforms the CMS auction.  Copyright 2012, Oxford University Press.
